%% ModelMesh Serving - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
%% Source: architecture/rhoai-2.6/modelmesh-serving.md

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant OAuthProxy as oauth-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant RESTProxy as REST Proxy<br/>(optional)
    participant ModelMesh as ModelMesh Sidecar (mm)<br/>8033/TCP gRPC
    participant Runtime as Runtime Container<br/>(Model Server)
    participant Puller as Storage Helper<br/>8086/TCP gRPC
    participant S3 as Object Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant etcd as etcd<br/>2379/TCP gRPC
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Controller as modelmesh-controller

    Note over Client,Runtime: Flow 1: gRPC Inference Request
    Client->>ModelMesh: gRPC inference request<br/>8033/TCP, TLS (optional), mTLS (optional)
    ModelMesh->>Runtime: Forward to runtime<br/>gRPC in-pod (plaintext)
    Runtime-->>ModelMesh: Prediction result
    ModelMesh-->>Client: gRPC response

    Note over Client,Runtime: Flow 2: REST Inference via oauth-proxy
    Client->>OAuthProxy: HTTPS POST /v1/models/...<br/>8443/TCP, TLS 1.2+, OAuth/SAR
    OAuthProxy->>RESTProxy: Forward (plaintext in-pod)
    RESTProxy->>ModelMesh: gRPC translate<br/>8033/TCP, TLS (if enabled)
    ModelMesh->>Runtime: Forward to runtime<br/>gRPC in-pod (plaintext)
    Runtime-->>ModelMesh: Prediction result
    ModelMesh-->>RESTProxy: gRPC response
    RESTProxy-->>OAuthProxy: HTTP response
    OAuthProxy-->>Client: HTTPS response

    Note over Controller,etcd: Flow 3: Predictor Reconciliation (VModel Registration)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch Predictor/InferenceService CRs<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: CR event notification
    Controller->>ModelMesh: SetVModel / DeleteVModel<br/>8033/TCP gRPC, TLS/mTLS (optional)
    ModelMesh->>etcd: Store VModel state<br/>2379/TCP gRPC, TLS, user/pass
    etcd-->>ModelMesh: Confirmation
    ModelMesh-->>Controller: VModel status

    Note over ModelMesh,S3: Flow 4: Model Loading (Storage Helper)
    ModelMesh->>Puller: Load model request<br/>8086/TCP gRPC (plaintext in-pod)
    Puller->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, TLS 1.2+, storage creds
    S3-->>Puller: Model artifacts
    Puller-->>ModelMesh: Model loaded (emptyDir)
    ModelMesh->>Runtime: Load model into runtime
    Runtime-->>ModelMesh: Model ready
